item.title: What does this do? (never seen before)
item.dc:creator: @Ashi Ashi
item.description:
@Ashi wrote:

It does nothing. You know that sometimes if you use a .bat to compile your server it might give you warnings? Warnings such as unused variable. In eclipse it would underline the unused variable/method or whatever with a yellow line.

@SuppressWarnings(“unused”) - basically tells the compiler that you know it’s unused so ignore the warning.
